13/09/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The State Investigation and Protection Agency's (SIPA) Special Support Unit celebrated its first anniversary Tuesday (12 September), with a ceremony in Eastern Sarajevo, attended by SIPA chief Sredoje Novic and EU Police Mission chief Vincenzo Coppola.
Several drills demonstrating procedures for apprehending dangerous criminals and terrorists were conducted as part of the celebration.
In a speech, Novic voiced confidence that BiH has trained professionals capable of contributing to international efforts against organised crime and terrorism.
(Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 13/09/06)
